cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the challenges of building recommender systems for highly subjective content, specifically digital art. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as the paper focuses on modeling rich content in terms of its visual appearance. Additionally, the paper mentions social dynamics, such as preferences towards certain art styles and artists, which could fall under the Social and Information Sciences (cs.SI) and Social Networks and the Web (cs.SD) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses temporal dynamics in terms of how users prefer visually consistent content within and across sessions, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
